PN,44301
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FStormont ministers could make
OL,8,Fdecisions which would unlock up to
OL,9,F#3.3 billion in additional spending
OL,10,Fpower each year, a Treasury analysis
OL,11,Fof Northern Ireland's finances has
OL,12,Fconcluded.
OL,14,FThe Open Book Review of Northern
OL,15,FIreland Executive Budget said if
OL,16,Fpowersharing ministers had taken
OL,17,Fforward "even an eighth" of options
OL,18,Favailable to them, they might have
OL,19,Favoided a budget overspend in the last
OL,20,Ffinancial year.
OL,26,@yD@IOUyD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FThe report examined a number of
OL,8,Foptions which could "improve the
OL,9,Fsustainability of the Northern Ireland
OL,10,Fbudget".
OL,12,FIts conclusions identify "a persistent
OL,13,Fgap between Northern Ireland Executive
OL,14,Fspending and available funding".
OL,16,FFirst Minister Michelle O'Neill said
OL,17,Fthe report had the "wrong starting
OL,18,Fpoint" and deputy First Minister Ms
OL,19,FLittle-Pengelly said it was a "missed
OL,20,Fopportunity".
OL,26,@pD@UOUrD@GO]tD@ZOUvD@_O]yD@TOUzD@FO]{D@
OL,26,A_OU|D@LO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FThe deputy First Minister also
OL,8,Fdescribed some of the findings of the
OL,9,Freview as "absolutely preposterous".
OL,11,FIt says this is due to a number of
OL,12,Ffactors including public service
OL,13,F"inefficiencies", policy decisions to
OL,14,Fmaintain a "large public sector
OL,15,Fworkforce" and pay parity with the
OL,16,Frest of the UK, and policy decisions
OL,17,Fto put in place "super-parity measures
OL,18,Fcompared to the UK Government".
OL,26,@qD@KOUqD@cO]uD@AOUuD@PO]vD@LOUwD@JO]yD@
OL,26,AQOUzD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FNorthern Ireland's political leaders
OL,8,Frecently called for a meeting with
OL,9,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer amid
OL,10,Fconcerns about the financial situation
OL,11,Ffacing Stormont departments and with a
OL,12,Fbudget still not agreed.
OL,14,FHowever, the report focused on
OL,15,Fspending in the current Northern
OL,16,FIreland budget allocation.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FIn February, the UK Government
OL,8,Fannounced it would make #400 million
OL,9,Favailable from reserves for the
OL,10,FExecutive to deal with overspend
OL,11,Fpressures in health and education.
OL,13,FThe money has to be repaid over the
OL,14,Fnext three years and the Treasury said
OL,15,Fit would be conducting an "open-book
OL,16,Fexercise" looking at the Executive
OL,17,Fbudget.
OL,26,@wD@[OUxD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FStormont's Finance Committee was told
OL,8,Flast week that that report had been
OL,9,Fshared with Executive ministers. An
OL,10,Fofficial said it would be used to
OL,11,F"inform discussions" with the Treasury.
OL,13,FThe Treasury report said it is to
OL,14,F"inform the Executive's decisions on
OL,15,Ffunding allocations".
OL,26,@sD@AOUsD@TO]vD@AOUwD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FIt pointed out that for every #1 the
OL,8,FUK Government spends on comparable
OL,9,Fpublic services in England, the
OL,10,FNorthern Ireland Executive has "at
OL,11,Fleast #1.24 to spend" to reflect
OL,12,F"Northern Ireland's higher levels of
OL,13,Frelative need".
OL,15,FBut it said for a number of
OL,16,Fdepartments "funding per head is
OL,17,Fsignificantly in excess of 124% of
OL,18,Fcomparable spend by the UK Government".
OL,26,@rD@`OUsD@UO]tD@AOUuD@NO]xD@MOUzD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FThe report said health spending per
OL,8,Fhead in Northern Ireland is 152% of
OL,9,Fthat in England, policing is at 166%
OL,10,Fand schools at 140%.
OL,12,FIt added that across the whole of the
OL,13,Fjustice system, spending is at 120%
OL,14,Fcompared with the rest of the UK.
OL,16,FThe report said: "As a sense of scale,
OL,17,Fhealth spending of 124% of comparable
OL,18,Fspending in England would be #1.3
OL,19,Fbillion lower than current spending on
OL,20,Fhealth.
OL,26,@xD@ROU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,F"Similarly, 124% of comparable
OL,8,Fspending in England on education would
OL,9,Fbe #424 million lower than current
OL,10,Fspending on education."
OL,12,FThe report said the "Executive's
OL,13,Fpolicy decisions may also be creating
OL,14,Fpressures elsewhere in the budget".
OL,16,FIt added that the Executive spends a
OL,17,Fhigher share of Resource Departmental
OL,18,FExpenditure Limit (RDEL) on public
OL,19,Fsector pay than the UK Government.
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@WO]tD@UOUvD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FThe report said: "If the Executive's
OL,8,Fpay bill was even halfway between the
OL,9,Fcurrent proportion of RDEL spent on
OL,10,Fpay in NI and the UK Government's this
OL,11,Fwould realise a saving of up to #1.25
OL,12,Fbillion RDEL which could be spent on
OL,13,Fnon-pay public service delivery."
OL,26,@oD@ROUuD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FIt also estimated that offering lower
OL,8,Fdomestic rates and higher rates relief
OL,9,Fin Northern Ireland than the UK
OL,10,FGovernment does in England "costs the
OL,11,FExecutive around #639 million a year
OL,12,Fin revenue foregone with a further
OL,13,F#684 million a year from other
OL,14,Fmeasures where the Executive is not
OL,15,Fimplementing the same fees and charges
OL,16,Fas the UK Government".
OL,26,@rD@\OUxD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FIt said: "In total, this report
OL,8,Fassesses that, were the Executive to
OL,9,Fpursue even a subset of the options
OL,10,Fset out, it could unlock up to #3.3
OL,11,Fbillion in addition spending power.
OL,13,F"The Executive would not need to adopt
OL,14,Fall of these options but taking
OL,15,Fforward even an eighth of these
OL,16,Foptions (by value) may have avoided
OL,17,Fthe need for a reserve claim in 2025-
OL,18,F26."
OL,26,@oD@JOUuD@AOUzD@DO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44313
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FThe report contains sections examining
OL,8,Fpublic sector reforms and
OL,9,Fefficiencies, public sector pay and
OL,10,Fpotential revenue-raising measures.
OL,12,FIt said that introducing domestic
OL,13,Fwater charges "could raise significant
OL,14,Fadditional revenue for the Northern
OL,15,FIreland Executive".
OL,17,FThe report said: "The Northern Ireland
OL,18,FExecutive could raise over #357
OL,19,Fmillion per annum if households were
OL,20,Fcharged the same as households in
OL,21,FEngland and Wales."
OL,26,@uD@OOUwD@RO]yD@ROU}D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G13/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44314
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FIt estimated that introducing
OL,8,Fprescription charges at a similar rate
OL,9,Fto England could raise more than #24
OL,10,Fmillion and removing free bus travel
OL,11,Ffor people aged between 60 and 64
OL,12,Fcould raise #13 million.
OL,14,FThe report added: "Increasing tuition
OL,15,Ffees could reduce the need to
OL,16,Fsubsidise the university sector for
OL,17,Fteaching and research with Executive
OL,18,FDEL funding, providing the Executive
OL,19,Fwith up to an additional #237 million
OL,20,Fto support wider public services."
OL,26,@vD@SOU|D@bO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G14/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44315
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FThe report pointed out that decisions
OL,8,Fon spending are for the powersharing
OL,9,FExecutive ministers who "will want to
OL,10,Fconsider the delivery options and
OL,11,Ftimescales".
OL,13,FIt adds: "Given the scale of
OL,14,Foverspends (#467.6 million in 2025-
OL,15,F26), the Executive would not need to
OL,16,Fconsider all of these options or to
OL,17,Ffully mirror policies in other parts
OL,18,Fof the UK to balance their budget.
OL,26,@qD@YOUsD@KO]uD@JOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G15/17
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44316
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1776787870
OL,3,CStormont decisions could unlock #3.3bn
OL,4,Cin spending power, Treasury review
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,F"If these options are pursued by the
OL,8,FExecutive, they would improve the
OL,9,Fsustainability of the Northern Ireland
OL,10,Fbudget.
OL,12,F"They could also release significant
OL,13,Fadditional funding to speed up the
OL,14,Ftransformation of public services and
OL,15,Fimprove outcomes for people in
OL,16,FNorthern Ireland."
